node.text: On the latest episode of Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) heads to his hometown of Buffalo, New York to learn how to make three different summertime cocktails from head bartender at Lloyd Taco Factory (@lloydtacofactory), Jon Wheelock (@jwheels1). We won't give away what they're making, but we will say, if gin is your spirit of choice, you're in for a treat. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Elevate Your Next Summer Get-together With These Cocktail Recipes

node.text: Introducing Sipping With, a new series hosted by Contributing Editor Sean Flynn (@travelingnewyorker), who’s taking us behind the bar at world-renowned restaurants, hotels, and resorts to see how the best in the business craft specialty cocktails. On this episode, Sean visits @themarkhotelny, where Bartender Ken Ziegler shows us how to make a ginger margarita — a fresh take on the classic. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Learn How One of the Best Hotels in NYC Makes Its Signature Margarita

node.text: In the latest installment of our Walk With T+L series, you can tour Disney World's Magic Kingdom with an Imagineer and uncover the design secrets you might have missed during your last visit. We’ll visit the exclusive Cinderella Castle Suite, the Beauty and the Beast-themed Be Our Guest Restaurant, and so much more. Come along as we get an inside look at how Disney “makes magic real” — the theme of the Magic Kingdom.

node.title: Uncover the Magic Kingdom's Design Secrets With a Disney Imagineer

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: the island of Amorgos, Greece. The Greek Islands are on just about everyone's bucket list. But like many of the world’s most photogenic destinations, over-tourism has become a real issue. Luckily, there are more than 200 inhabited islands in Greece, meaning you can get all of the beauty and none the crowds on some of the lesser-known islands, like Amorgos. Come along! Tour by @_thebluewalk

node.title: This Greek Island Has All of the Beauty and None of the Crowds

node.text:
This week on Behind the Views: Tiffany Nguyen (@tiffpenguin). When Tiffany first became interested in photography, she was actually studying something quite far from it: dentistry. Nonetheless, she was inspired by the beautiful destination images she saw on Instagram, so she started exploring nearby national parks and capturing the scenery. “With each subsequent trip, I would feel more and more comfortable taking photos. For me, spending time in the outdoors and capturing my adventures went hand in hand,” she says.
.
When asked about her first trip as a travel photographer, Tiffany says, “I’ll never forget my first trip to Yosemite. The enormous scale of the sights was like nowhere else I had ever seen. I was in awe of the world around me like never before. I remember taking so many photos because I just couldn’t get enough. From epic views of Half Dome to the tallest waterfall in North America, Yosemite really has it all.”
.
Tiffany’s advice for aspiring photographers: “When you’re first starting off, you don’t have to travel far and wide to get the best shots. Some of my favorite photos were taken just a short drive from home. Start in your own backyard and explore places nearby first while you work on your craft. This really makes you appreciate the places you travel and never take anything for granted.”
.
In Tiffany’s go-to camera bag you’ll find a DJI Air 2S, Sony a1 camera, and 16-35mm f2.8, 24-70 mm f2.8, 70-200mm f4, and 35mm f1.4 lenses.
.
All photos by @tiffpenguin

node.text: On the latest episode of Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) heads to his hometown of Buffalo, New York to learn how to make three different summertime cocktails from head bartender at Lloyd Taco Factory (@lloydtacofactory), Jon Wheelock (@jwheels1). We won't give away what they're making, but we will say, if gin is your spirit of choice, you're in for a treat. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!
